- "demographic tapestry" refers to the comprehensive demographic data across regions and income groups;
- "beacons of longevity" metaphorically refers to regions and income groups with the highest life expectancy;
- "peak of life expectancy" refers to the maximum life expectancy;
- "average horizon of human years" refers to the average life expectancy across all regions and income groups.

- 'Lower middle income' refers to countries with a gross national income per capita between $1,046 and $4,095;
- 'Africa' is a continent with 54 recognized sovereign states;
- 'ISO 3166-1 alpha-3' is a three-letter country code that uniquely identifies each country.

- "vibrant and growing" refers to regions with an average population growth rate higher than the global average;
- "the global heartbeat" refers to the average population growth rate of all countries;
- "average median age" is the median age of the population averaged across all countries in the region;
- "life expectancy" is the average life expectancy of the population in the region.

- 'Recent population growth' indicates the population increase from the previous year to the most recent year of available data;
- 'Life expectancy over 70 years' refers to the average number of years a person is expected to live, which is above 70;
- 'Median age above 30' refers to the age at which half of the population is older and half is younger, which is above 30.

- "Large population" refers to countries with a total population greater than 30 million;
- "Non-projected data" refers to data where `is_projection = 0`, indicating that the data is based on actual recorded statistics rather than future projections;
- "Average life expectancy" is the mean life expectancy calculated for each region.

- "Relatively young population" refers to countries where the median age is greater than 18;
- "High birth rates" refers to countries where the birth rate is greater than 30 per 1,000 population;
- "Average life expectancy exceeds 60 years" refers to the condition that the average life expectancy must be greater than 60.

- "ISO 3166-1 alpha-3" is a three-letter code that uniquely identifies countries;
- "Geographical region" refers to the broad geographic area where the country is located;
- "Life expectancy" is the average number of years a person is expected to live based on statistical data.

- 'Heart of their population' refers to the median age;
- 'Bloom to an average greater than 20 years' means the average median age is greater than 20;
- 'Dawn of the millennium' refers to the year 2000;
- 'Twilight of 2020' refers to the year 2020.

- 'Low income' refers to countries with a low-income economy as classified by the World Bank;
- 'population_growth_rate' is the annual percentage increase in the population;
- 'most recent demographic data' refers to the latest available data for each country.

- "Rapid population growth" refers to the highest population growth rate;
- "Sprinter leading the race in a marathon of demographic shifts" refers to the country with the highest average yearly population change;
- "Average yearly population change" is calculated as the average percentage change in population from one year to the next.

- "youthful countries" refers to countries where the median age of the population is between 15 and 25;
- "bloom of youth" is a metaphorical expression for ages between 15 and 25, representing a period of young adulthood;
- "global average" refers to the average population across all countries in the dataset.

- "growing more rapidly than the average" refers to a population growth rate greater than 2;
- "wiser beyond their years" refers to a median age greater than the average median age across all countries;
- "where the population's wisdom and numbers surpass the global average" refers to an average total population greater than the average total population across all countries.

- "most recent data" refers to the latest year for which demographic data is available for each country;
- "population exceeding 30 million" means the total estimated population is more than 30,000,000;
- "median age above 18" means the median age of the population is greater than 18 years.

- "Beacons of longevity" refers to countries with the highest life expectancy within their regions;
- "Pillars of gender balance" refers to countries with the highest gender ratio (male to female) within their income groups;
- Life expectancy is a measure of the average lifespan of individuals in a population;
- Gender ratio is the ratio of males to females in a population, often used to assess demographic balance.
